&lt;p&gt;According to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://flink.apache.org/downloads.html#update-policy-for-old-releases&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;release update policy&lt;/a&gt;, the community provides bugfixes only for the latest release and the one before it. That means this should be fixed for 1.12, 1.13 and of course the upcoming 1.14 releases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usually, the contributors only need to open PRs against the master branch and the committers will port the changes to the old release branches if needed. For this ticket, we probably need an additional PR against 1.12, because we have switched our document framework from Ruby to Hugo since1.13.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
